title: Armor vs. Sticker - Rhino Trunks
description: A quick look at the differences between Rhino Armor and Rhino Sticker trunks.

asset.author: Trunk Outlet
asset.hookText: A quick look at the differences between Rhino Armor and Rhino Sticker trunks. http://www.trunkoutlet.com

transcripts: Rhino trunks come in a variety of looks including the armor and the sticker trunk. From the distance its harder to tell the difference between these two. Here the armor trunk is on the left while the sticker trunk is on the right. The armored trucks have an exterior of a nylon which creates a fabric feel in the traditional look. The sticker trunk exterior is that of vinyl coated polyester which makes for a smoother feel. The sticker trunk also allows for decals or stickers to be placed on the trunk and the trunk itself can also be painted. Both the Armor and the sticker trunks are constructed of the same material otherwise as you can see here
